On July 15, 2016, the President signed into law several bills, including H.R. 636, which extends authorization for Federal Aviation Administration programs and related revenue authorities until September 30, 2017. H.R. 3766 requires the President to establish guidelines for measurable goals, performance metrics, and monitoring and evaluation plans for specific U.S. foreign assistance programs. H.R. 4372 designates a United States Postal Service facility in Bergen, New York, as the Barry G. Miller Post Office. H.R. 4960 designates a United States Postal Service facility in Aurora, Illinois, as the Kenneth M. Christy Post Office Building. Finally, S. 2845 extends sanctions on individuals responsible for human rights violations in Venezuela until December 2019.